    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="1366"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1366">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1627</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the</hi>
                    <gloss type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                    </gloss>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 25, 1915</hi>.</date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>648. Your 629, March 12, 5 p. m.<note n="1" xml:id="d1366fn1">See footnote 1, <hi
                            rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_964">p. 964</ref>.</note>
                    Foreign Office note received to-day, replies that as conditions of the eventual
                    occupation of Constantinople as result of present operations in Dardanelles
                    depend essentially upon the events of war and cannot be determined in advance,
                    it is impossible for French Government to accept proposal in question.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
